 343:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * @param channel Constant pointer to USIC channel handle of type @ref XMC_USIC_CH_t \n
 344:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * 				   \b Range: @ref XMC_UART0_CH0, XMC_UART0_CH1 ,XMC_UART1_CH0, XMC_UART1_CH1, XMC_UART2_CH0,
 345:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * @param rate Desired baudrate. \n
 346:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  *           \b Range: minimum value = 100, maximum value depends on the peripheral clock frequency
 347:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * 				   and \a oversampling. Maximum baudrate can be derived using the formula: (fperiph * 1023)/
 348:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * @param  oversampling Required oversampling. The value indicates the number of time quanta for on
 349:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * 					 This can be related to the number of samples for each logic state of the data signal.\n
 350:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * 					 \b Range: 4 to 32. Value should be chosen based on the protocol used.
 351:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * @return XMC_UART_CH_STATUS_t Status indicating the baudrate configuration.\n
 352:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * 			     \b Range: @ref XMC_USIC_CH_STATUS_OK if baudrate is successfully configured,
 353:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * 					 @ref XMC_USIC_CH_STATUS_ERROR if desired baudrate or oversampling is invalid.
 354:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  *
