 369:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * 				   \b Range: @ref XMC_UART0_CH0, XMC_UART0_CH1 ,XMC_UART1_CH0, XMC_UART1_CH1, XMC_UART2_CH0,
 370:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * @param rate Desired baudrate. \n
 371:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  *           \b Range: minimum value = 100, maximum value depends on the peripheral clock frequency
 372:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * 				   and \a oversampling. Maximum baudrate can be derived using the formula: (fperiph * 1023)/
 373:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * @param  oversampling Required oversampling. The value indicates the number of time quanta for on
 374:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * 					 This can be related to the number of samples for each logic state of the data signal.\n
 375:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * 					 \b Range: 4 to 32. Value should be chosen based on the protocol used.
 376:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * @param normal_divider_mode Selects normal divider mode for baudrate generator instead of default
 377:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * @return XMC_UART_CH_STATUS_t Status indicating the baudrate configuration.\n
 378:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * 			     \b Range: @ref XMC_USIC_CH_STATUS_OK if baudrate is successfully configured,
 379:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * 					 @ref XMC_USIC_CH_STATUS_ERROR if desired baudrate or oversampling is invalid.
 380:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  *
 381:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * \par<b>Description:</b><br>
 382:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * Sets the bus speed in bits per second.\n\n
 383:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * Derives the values of \a STEP and PDIV to arrive at the optimum realistic speed possible.
 384:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * \a oversampling is the number of samples to be taken for each symbol of UART protocol.
 385:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * Default \a oversampling of 16 is considered if the input \a oversampling is less than 4. It is r
 386:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * a minimum oversampling of 4 for UART.
 387:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  *
 388:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * \par<b>Related APIs:</b><BR>
 389:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * XMC_UART_CH_Init(), XMC_UART_CH_Stop(), XMC_USIC_CH_GetBaudrate()
 390:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  */
 391:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h **** XMC_UART_CH_STATUS_t XMC_UART_CH_SetBaudrateEx(XMC_USIC_CH_t *const channel, uint32_t rate, uint32_
 392:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h **** 
 393:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h **** /**
 394:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * @param channel Constant pointer to USIC channel handle of type @ref XMC_USIC_CH_t \n
 395:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * 				  \b Range: @ref XMC_UART0_CH0, @ref XMC_UART0_CH1,@ref XMC_UART1_CH0,@ref XMC_UART1_CH1,@re
 396:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * @param  data Data to be transmitted. \n
 397:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  *          \b Range: 16 bit unsigned data within the range 0 to 65535. Actual size of
 398:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  *          data transmitted depends on the configured number of bits for the UART protocol in the 
 399:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * @return None
 400:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  *
 401:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * \par<b>Description</b><br>
 402:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * Transmits data over serial communication channel using UART protocol.\n\n
 403:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * Based on the channel configuration, data is either put to the transmit FIFO or to TBUF register.
 404:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * Before putting data to TBUF, the API waits for TBUF to finish shifting its contents to shift reg
 405:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * So user can continuously execute the API without checking for TBUF busy status. Based on the num
 406:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * data bits configured, the lower significant bits will be extracted for transmission.
 407:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  *
 408:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * Note: When FIFO is not configured, the API waits for the TBUF to be available.
 409:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * This makes the execution a blocking call.
 410:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  *
 411:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * \par<b>Related APIs:</b><BR>
 412:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * XMC_UART_CH_GetReceivedData() \n\n\n
 413:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  */
 414:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h **** void XMC_UART_CH_Transmit(XMC_USIC_CH_t *const channel, const uint16_t data);
 415:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h **** 
 416:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h **** /**
 417:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * @param channel Constant pointer to USIC channel handle of type @ref XMC_USIC_CH_t \n
 418:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * 				  \b Range: @ref XMC_UART0_CH0, @ref XMC_UART0_CH1,@ref XMC_UART1_CH0,@ref XMC_UART1_CH1,@re
 419:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * @return uint16_t Received data over UART communication channel.
 420:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * \par<b>Description</b><br>
 421:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * Provides one word of data received over UART communication channel.\n\n
 422:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * Based on the channel configuration, data is either read from the receive FIFO or RBUF register.
 423:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * Before returning the value, there is no check for data validity. User should check the appropria
 424:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * data receive flags(standard receive/alternative receive/FIFO standard receive/FIFO alternative r
 425:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * before executing the API. Reading from an empty receive FIFO can generate a receive error event.
 426:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  *
 427:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * \par<b>Related APIs:</b><BR>
 428:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * XMC_UART_CH_GetStatusFlag(), XMC_UART_CH_Transmit() \n\n\n
 429:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  */
 430:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h **** uint16_t XMC_UART_CH_GetReceivedData(XMC_USIC_CH_t *const channel);
 431:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h **** 
 432:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h **** /**
 433:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * @param  channel Constant pointer to USIC channel handle of type @ref XMC_USIC_CH_t \n
 434:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * 				  \b Range: @ref XMC_UART0_CH0, @ref XMC_UART0_CH1,@ref XMC_UART1_CH0,@ref XMC_UART1_CH1,@re
 435:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * @param  word_length Data word length. \n
 436:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  *          \b Range: minimum= 1, maximum= 16.
 437:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * @return None
 438:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  *
 439:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * \par<b>Description</b><br>
 440:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * Sets the data word length in number of bits.\n\n
 441:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * Word length can range from 1 to 16. It indicates the number of data bits in a data word.
 442:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * The value of \a word_length will be decremented by 1 before setting the value to \a SCTR registe
 443:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * If the UART data bits is more than 16, then the frame length should be set to the actual number 
 444:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * word length should be configured with the number of bits expected in each transaction. For examp
 445:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * for UART communication is 20 bits, then the frame length should be set as 20. Word length can be
 446:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * transmit and receive handling. If data is stored as 8bit array, then the word length can be set 
 447:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * a full message of UART data should be transmitted/ received as 3 data words.
 448:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  *
 449:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * \par<b>Related APIs:</b><BR>
 450:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  * XMC_UART_CH_SetFrameLength() \n\n\n
 451:D:/Infineon/Tools/DAVE IDE/4.5.0.202105191637/eclipse/workspace/XMC4300-boot/Libraries/XMCLib/inc\xmc_uart.h ****  */
